y-access | critical | planned | unresolved | needs-target-search |  | declaration-candidate | Media library and album discovery |  | platform capability status is still planned |\n36: \n37: ## Instructions\n38: \n39: - If any entry is unresolved, run a capability resolution session before phase implementation.\n40: - Capability resolution may update only platform-capability-check.json/md.\n41: - A real HarmonyOS/Cangjie API, Kit, example, or package must be used when available; do not close with local mock, in-memory data, sample data, or generic fallback.\n42: - Use resolved-deferred only after checking CangjieSkills/HarmonyOS/Cangjie docs, HarmonyOS-Examples, SDK declarations, and package lookup when relevant.\n43: - Use capability-sdk-probe-cache.json as preparation evidence for SDK declaration/library candidates; it is not authority by itself.\n44: - Treat ArkTS/native/overview declarations as discovery-only until a Cangjie-callable API, wrapper, FFI, bridge, or compile probe is recorded.\n45: - When compileProbeRecommended is true, run a bounded target-context compile probe or record the concrete SDK/tooling blocker before phase implementation.\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Phase Platform Capability Pre-Resolution\n\n- Phase: `phase-04-home-history`\n\n## Purpose\n\nPhase-scoped platform capability pre-resolution checklist. This is generated from phase-task-checklist.json and platform-capability-check.json before phase implementation. All current-phase critical/high platform capabilities must be resolved before target code edits begin.\n\n## Summary\n\n| metric | value |\n| --- | --- |\n| phasePlatformCapabilities | 1 |\n| unresolvedPlatformCapabilities | 1 |\n| compileProbeRecommendedCapabilities | 0 |\n| discoveryOnlyCapabilities | 0 |\n| sdkProbeDeclarationCandidateCapabilities | 1 |\n\n## Resolution Status Counts\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"translation-inputs\\phase-capability-checklist.md","time":{"start":1782579102889,"end":1782579102928}},"id":"prt_f09fe84a8002kH9pCpD0xyrmsy","sessionID":"ses_0f601b585ffeXhzFroJg7XaNbQ","messageID":"msg_f09fe4b75001enwdnwPsNHDaT5"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782579102930,"sessionID":"ses_0f601b585ffeXhzFroJg7XaNbQ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_lcUMpwx8TF8bTQeEzHPGZIaN","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\platform-capability-check.md","limit":400,"offset":1},"output":"<path>D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\platform-capability-check.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Platform Capability Check\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This is the agent-maintained platform capability check. Before marking a critical/high platform capability as direct, replaced, fallback, or deferred, query CangjieSkills/HarmonyOS/Cangjie API docs, HarmonyOS-Examples, or package index lookup such as `https://pkg.cangjie-lang.cn` and record the evidence in `targetCapabilitySearch`. Direct means callable from the Cangjie target; ArkTS-only or native-only declarations are discovery evidence until an already planned or existing Cangjie wrapper, FFI, or bridge is verified with target build evidence. Use cjpm/project-management docs only to configure a chosen dependency.\n6: \n7: ## Status Values\n8: \n9: `deferred`, `implemented-fallback`, `not-applicable`, `not-covered`, `planned`, `platform-replaced`, `unreviewed`, `verified-direct`\n10: \n11: ## Deferred Required Fields\n12: \n13: `targetCapabilitySearch`, `blocker`, `targetFallback`, `futureCompletionPath`\n14: \n15: ## Entries\n16: \n17: | capability id | status | phase | importance | decision | probe | capability | target API/library | strategy |\n18: | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n19: | media-library-access | planned | phase-04-home-history | critical | needs-target-search |  | Media library and album discovery |  |  |\n20: | file-access-and-saf | planned | phase-05-detail-cart | critical | needs-target-search |  | File access, document permissions, and share URIs |  |  |\n21: | image-viewer-gestures | planned | phase-05-detail-cart | critical | needs-target-search |  | Image viewer gestures and metadata |  |  |\n22: | localization-resources | verified-direct | phase-01-project-skeleton-resources | high | resolved-real-api |  | Localized resources and formatted strings | HarmonyOS Cangjie LocalizationKit resource model (`ohos.base.ResourceStr`, `ohos.resource.AppResource`, `ohos.resource_manager.ResourceManager`) with standard HarmonyOS `string.json`/`color.json` resources | Phase 01 migrates Android labels, start-window colors, and resource-backed UI text into HarmonyOS descriptor/resource files, with AppResource helpers for Cangjie access where needed. Batch 3 also removes hard-coded route-shell labels by routing them through `foodike_resources.cj` and `app_router.cj` before display in `bootstrap_page.cj`. |\n23: | runtime-permissions | not-applicable | phase-02-startup-session-navigation | high | resolved-not-applicable |  | Runtime permissions and protected platform access | HarmonyOS Cangjie AbilityKit permission APIs exist (`ohos.ability_access_ctrl.AtManager`, `ohos.security.permission_request_result.PermissionRequestResult`) but are not required by phase-02 startup/session/navigation source behavior. | Treat the phase-02 permission requirement as a source-analysis false positive. Do not add permission prompts or protected-access scaffolding during startup/session/navigation implementation unless later source-backed phases introduce real protected APIs. |\n24: | background-and-platform-components | platform-replaced | phase-02-startup-session-navigation | high | resolved-platform-replacement |  | Background work, services, receivers, widgets, and notifications | HarmonyOS Cangjie AbilityKit app-entry APIs (`ohos.app.ability.ui_ability.UIAbility`, `UIAbilityContext`, `Want`) plus ArkUI `Navigation`/`NavPathStack` or `Router` for in-app startup and route flow | Resolve the source Android platform component surface as a HarmonyOS platform replacement: model app startup in the target `UIAbility`/descriptor entry, keep splash-like gating inside bootstrap state before rendering the main route, and implement onboarding/home navigation using the existing ArkUI route shell instead of Android `Application`, `ComponentActivity`, and `core-splashscreen` APIs. |\n\n(End of file - total 24 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Platform Capability Check\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis is the agent-maintained platform capability check. Before marking a critical/high platform capability as direct, replaced, fallback, or deferred, query CangjieSkills/HarmonyOS/Cangjie API docs, HarmonyOS-Examples, or package index lookup such as `https://pkg.cangjie-lang.cn` and record the evidence in `targetCapabilitySearch`. Direct means callable from the Cangjie target; ArkTS-only or native-only declarations are discovery evidence until an already planned or existing Cangjie wrapper, FFI, or bridge is verified with target build evidence. Use cjpm/project-management docs only to configure a chosen dependency.\n\n## Status Values\n\n`deferred`, `implemented-fallback`, `not-applicable`, `not-covered`, `planned`, `platform-replaced`, `unreviewed`, `verified-direct`\n\n## Deferred Required Fields\n\n`targetCapabilitySearch`, `blocker`, `targetFallback`, `futureCompletionPath`\n\n## Entries\n\n| capability id | status | phase | importance | decision | probe | capability | target API/library | strategy |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| media-library-access | planned | phase-04-home-history | critical | needs-target-search |  | Media library and album discovery |  |  |\n| file-access-and-saf | planned | phase-05-detail-cart | critical | needs-target-search |  | File access, document permissions, and share URIs |  |  |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"translation-inputs\\platform-capability-check.md","time":{"start":1782579102902,"end":1782579102929}},"id":"prt_f09fe84b5001VT4Jwn7B6olvA5","sessionID":"ses_0f601b585ffeXhzFroJg7XaNbQ","messageID":"msg_f09fe4b75001enwdnwPsNHDaT5"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782579102931,"sessionID":"ses_0f601b585ffeXhzFroJg7XaNbQ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_z40HCqbyXPEJoE0TeiysTi9F","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\docs\\harmonyos-cangjie-translation-checklist.md","limit":400,"offset":1},"output":"<path>D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\docs\\harmonyos-cangjie-translation-checklist.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # HarmonyOS Cangjie Translation Checklist\n2: \n3: 面向 Android Java app 迁移到 HarmonyOS Cangjie 的阶段性检查表。它来自 Spendee 案例记录和后续构建修复经验，目标是在每个 `opencode-cj` phase 结束时先抓住高频编译/宏展开问题，再进入下一阶段。\n4: \n5: ## 使用时机\n6: \n7: 1. 每个翻译 phase 开始前，把本 phase 可能触及的条目加入 `opencode-cj` prompt。\n8: 2. 每个 phase 结束后，先运行完整构建门禁：\n9: \n10:    `<python>` 表示当前 Python 解释器：macOS/Linux 可用 `python3`，Windows 可用 `py -3` 或 `python`。\n11: \n12:    ```bash\n13:    <python> scripts/shared/reports/build_hap_report.py \\\n14:      --workspace-root <translation-workspace> \\\n15:      --target-project <target-project> \\\n16:      --phase <phase-name>\n17:    ```\n18: \n19: 3. 如果报告失败，把 `build-reports/<phase-name>/build-report.md` 和首个 blocker 交给 `opencode-cj` 修复当前 phase，不要先开启下一阶段。\n20: 4. 构建通过后，再进入运行时 smoke 或行为验证。\n21: \n22: ## 资源和字符串边界\n23: \n24: - 不要把 `@r(...)` / `AppResource` 直接当作普通 `String`。\n25: - UI prop 如果可能接收资源字符串，优先使用 `ResourceStr`，或在边界处做 SDK 支持的显式转换。\n26: - 不要对 `ResourceStr` 调用普通字符串方法，例如 `isEmpty()`；需要空态时使用独立 `Bool` 状态。\n27: - 迁移 Android `setText(...)` 时，确认 HarmonyOS 端有明确的状态赋值或可观察数据源驱动文本刷新。\n28: - 每次资源迁移后，检查 `string.json`、media 资源和实际 UI 引用，避免保留旧 placeholder key 或缺失 AppScope/entry 双层资源。\n29: \n30: ## Option 和控制流\n31: \n32: - 不要生成 Java/Kotlin 风格的 `Option.get()`。\n33: - 非 UI helper 中使用 `match`、显式 `case Some(...)` / `case None`，或当前 SDK 支持的安全访问 API。\n34: - UI 构建逻辑中避免直接让 `match` 分支裸露生成不兼容的 component 形态；需要时拆成命名 `@Builder`。\n35: - 启动/依赖注入状态建议拆成明确的 `Bool`、错误资源、服务 option 解包 helper，减少 `@Component` 宏失败面。\n36: \n37: ## 包结构和导入\n38: \n39: - 避免 root package 与 `pages` / `routing` 之间出现环形依赖。公共 route 类型优先放在 `routing` 或独立 models/helpers 包。\n40: - UI 文件中避免宽泛 `std.collection.*` 导入；它可能和 ArkUI 组件名冲突，例如 `Stack`。\n41: - 需要集合类型时优先显式导入或限定命名。\n42: - helper 类型如果会通过 public `@Component` 生成构造器暴露，确认类型本身也是必要的 public 可见性。\n43: - 不要把临时 template/cache 文件当成迁移输入；`.cache`、build output 和 diagnostic log 只作为诊断证据。\n44: \n45: ## ArkUI Component 和 Builder\n46: \n47: - `@BuilderParam` 优先传入命名 `@Builder` 方法，不要依赖未验证的 inline closure 或 trailing component block。\n48: - 自定义容器组件要按当前 SDK 支持的构造器/slot 形态实现，不能照搬 ArkTS 示例。\n49: - 校验 ArkUI named arguments 和 modifiers 来自当前 Cangjie HarmonyOS SDK 文档，而不是只参考 ArkTS。\n50: - 对 `@Component` macro 失败，先缩小到入口组件状态、构造器 public 类型、资源字符串类型和 `@Publish` 字段类型这四类高频根因。\n51: - 组件内部紧密相关的 owner state 文本可直接在 owning page builder 中渲染，避免子组件 prop 复用导致同会话文本不刷新。\n52: \n53: ## 状态和可观察集合\n54: \n55: - 路由和跨页面状态模型使用 SDK 支持的 `@Observed`、`@Publish` 和明确字段类型。\n56: - 需要列表变化驱动 UI 时，使用 `ObservedArrayList` 等 SDK 支持的数据源，并给 `ForEach` 提供稳定 key。\n57: - 不要假设 `ObservedArrayList` 是普通 iterator；辅助逻辑中用下标访问或 SDK 支持方法。\n58: - 跨组件变化的 prop 需要 `@Prop` / `@Link` / `@Watch` 等明确同步链路。\n59: - 对 primitive totals、余额、计数等关键展示值，保存/编辑/删除成功后优先执行明确赋值，避免只依赖持久化回读触发 UI。\n60: \n61: ## 测试迁移和验证\n62: \n63: - 源项目已有测试时，当前 phase 相关测试应迁移或改写为目标侧测试，验证翻译后的业务、数据、状态、资源或刷新行为。\n64: - 源项目没有测试时，应为核心可测试逻辑补充适量测试；源测试过少时，应优先补高风险行为测试。\n65: - 如果当前 SDK/模板不支持某类自动化测试，应保持代码可测试，并记录 deferred validation、替代验证方法和后续完成路径。\n66: - 不要为了通过构建直接删除、禁用或弱化已迁移/生成的测试；应修实现、修测试集成，或明确记录当前阶段测试限制。\n67: \n68: ## 构建配置和工具链\n69: \n70: - 完整 HAP 构建必须使用 DevEco Cangjie plugin 管理的 full SDK，例如 `~/.cangjie-sdk/<version>/cangjie`；standalone `~/.local/cangjie` 只能代表轻量 `cjc` / `cjpm` 可用。\n71: - 缺少 full SDK 时，应先安装/启用 DevEco Studio Cangjie plugin，再继续 full build gate。\n72: - 每阶段记录构建命令、失败阶段、首个 blocker 和已解决 blocker。\n73: - 常见阶段含义：\n74:   - `ohpm install`：依赖、registry、模板测试依赖或 oh-package 问题。\n75:   - `SyncCangjieResource`：资源生成、配置 schema、Cangjie build support 注入问题。\n76:   - `CompileCangjie`：Cangjie 语法、宏展开、包依赖、ArkUI API 问题。\n77:   - `PackageHap`：资源/loader/package 产物问题。\n78:   - `SignHap`：签名配置问题；未签名 debug HAP 通常可能只是 warning。\n79: - full build 通过前，不要把 standalone `cjpm check` 失败简单等同于 HAP 构建失败；两者依赖来源不同。\n80: \n81: ## opencode-cj 修复交接\n82: \n83: - `apply_patch` 失败后必须 read-back，因为失败可能部分落盘。\n84: - `L.map is not a function`、`apply_patch verification failed`、`Failed to read file to update` 要分开记录。\n85: - 长 phase 被打断或恢复时，先让 `opencode-cj` 检查文件系统当前状态，再继续，不要重复生成同名组件或服务。\n86: - 构建 blocker prompt 应包含：\n87:   - 当前 phase 名称。\n88:   - `build-report.md` 路径。\n89:   - 失败阶段。\n90:   - 首个 blocker message 和 location。\n91:   - 只修当前 phase blocker 的约束。\n92: \n93: ## Phase Gate 验收\n94: \n95: - `build_hap_report.py` 的 Markdown/JSON 报告存在。\n96: - 报告包含 command、result、failed stage、first blocker、warnings、HAP artifacts。\n97: - 如果失败，已有 `opencode-build-blocker-prompt.txt` 可直接交给 `opencode-cj`。\n98: - 如果成功，报告记录 full build gate 通过，且可把本 phase 的已知编译 blocker 标为 resolved。\n99: - 下一 phase 只能在构建通过，或用户明确批准带 blocker 继续时开始。\n100: \n101: ## Spendee 证据映射\n102: \n103: - `@r(...)` / `ResourceStr` 误用导致重复 generic inference 和 macro blocker。\n104: - `Option.get()` 在当前 SDK 下不可用，入口和服务解包需改为显式 `match`。\n105: - root/pages/routing 包循环会阻断 `CompileCangjie`。\n106: - UI 文件中的 `std.collection.*` 与 ArkUI `Stack` 名称冲突。\n107: - `@BuilderParam` 命名 builder 比 inline closure 更稳定。\n108: - `ObservedArrayList` 不能按普通 `for-in` 假设处理。\n109: - 同会话 finance totals 刷新最终需要 owner state、显式赋值和可观察列表配合，构建通过不能替代运行时刷新验证。\n110: - 如果 full SDK 在 Phase 1 就接入，许多 Cangjie/ArkUI 编译问题可以在引入当 phase 就暴露，而不是累积到最终构建。\n\n(End of file - total 110 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# HarmonyOS Cangjie Translation Checklist\n\n面向 Android Java app 迁移到 HarmonyOS Cangjie 的阶段性检查表。它来自 Spendee 案例记录和后续构建修复经验，目标是在每个 `opencode-cj` phase 结束时先抓住高频编译/宏展开问题，再进入下一阶段。\n\n## 使用时机\n\n1. 每个翻译 phase 开始前，把本 phase 可能触及的条目加入 `opencode-cj` prompt。\n2. 每个 phase 结束后，先运行完整构建门禁：\n\n   `<python>` 表示当前 Python 解释器：macOS/Linux 可用 `python3`，Windows 可用 `py -3` 或 `python`。\n\n   ```bash\n   <python> scripts/shared/reports/build_hap_report.py \\\n     --workspace-root <translation-workspace> \\\n     --target-project <target-project> \\\n     --phase <phase-name>\n   ```\n\n3. 如果报告失败，把 `build-reports/<phase-name>/build-report.md` 和首个 blocker 交给 `opencode-cj` 修复当前 phase，不要先开启下一阶段。\n4. 构建通过后，再进入运行时 smoke 或行为验证。","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"..\\..\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\docs\\harmonyos-cangjie-translation-checklist.md","time":{"start":1782579102885,"end":1782579102930}},"id":"prt_f09fe84a4002Of5U2b0tUY0z7z","sessionID":"ses_0f601b585ffeXhzFroJg7XaNbQ","messageID":"msg_f09fe4b75001enwdnwPsNHDaT5"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782579102934,"sessionID":"ses_0f601b585ffeXhzFroJg7XaNbQ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_OGq3MM0zQky1inyRsZGjajnL","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\task-planning.md","limit":400,"offset":1},"output":"<path>D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\task-planning.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Android Kotlin to HarmonyOS Cangjie Translation Plan\n2: \n3: ## Goal\n4: \n5: Translate the Android Kotlin project in `D:\\Kotlin2Cangjie\\Foodike` into a HarmonyOS Cangjie project rooted at `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\Foodike-Harmony`, preserving main features, screen flow, resources, state changes, data behavior, tests, and user-visible side effects while adapting implementation to HarmonyOS Cangjie patterns.\n6: \n7: ## Paths\n8: \n9: - App name: `Foodike`\n10: - Source kind: `kotlin`\n11: - Translation workspace: `D:\\workspace\\Foodike`\n12: - Workspace standing instructions: `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\AGENTS.md`\n13: - Source project: `D:\\Kotlin2Cangjie\\Foodike`\n14: - Target HarmonyOS Cangjie project: `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\Foodike-Harmony`\n15: - Translation inputs: `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs`\n16: - Translation records: `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-records`\n17: - Agent protocol: `D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\Kotlin2Cangjie\\docs\\android-kotlin-to-cangjie-agent-protocol.md`\n18: - HarmonyOS Cangjie checklist: `D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\docs\\harmonyos-cangjie-translation-checklist.md`\n19: \n20: ## Role Split\n21: \n22: - The source project is read-only behavior evidence.\n23: - The target project is the only application source tree that `opencode-cj` may modify.\n24: - `translation-inputs/` may contain generated reports, static analysis from separate Kotlin/Android analysis tools and Gradle metadata export, mapcir reference artifacts, and the agent-maintained `source-coverage-matrix.json/md` and `platform-capability-check.json/md`. Treat generated reports as read-only planning evidence; update only the source coverage matrix and platform capability check when recording migration coverage status.\n25: - The mapcir output, when present, is a deterministic bootstrap/reference artifact. Use it for project structure, resources, dependencies, and initial skeleton only. Do not treat generated placeholders as final business logic.\n26: - The workflow scripts orchestrate preparation and validation only; `opencode-cj` performs semantic translation and build repair.\n27: \n28: ## Structured Inputs\n29: \n30: Always review these generated baseline inputs when present:\n31: \n32: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/source-discovery.md`\n33: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/plan-seed.md`\n34: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/plan-seed.json`\n35: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/source-feature-survey.md`\n36: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/source-file-inventory.md`\n37: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix.md`\n38: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix-report.md`\n39: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/verification-results.md`\n40: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\phase-task-checklist.md` when a phase session is running\n41: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/platform-capability-check.md`\n42: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/platform-capability-check-report.md`\n43: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/target-structure-report.md`\n44: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/resource-coverage-report.md`\n45: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/coverage-gap-report.md`\n46: \n47: Then inspect relevant files from the unified inventory:\n48: \n49: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/source-discovery.json`\n50: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/source-discovery.md`\n51: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/mapcir/*.mapcir.json`\n52: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/mapcir/*.hybrid.mapcir.json`\n53: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/mapcir/skeleton/`\n54: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/mapcir/skeleton-hybrid/`\n55: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/unified-preparation-report.json`\n56: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/unified-preparation-report.md`\n57: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/preflight-report.md`\n58: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/platform-profile.json`\n59: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/sdk-report.json`\n60: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/skills-report.md`\n61: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/skills-report.json`\n62: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/source-feature-survey.md`\n63: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/source-feature-survey.json`\n64: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/source-file-inventory.md`\n65: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/source-file-inventory.json`\n66: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/agent-source-walkthrough.md`\n67: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/plan-seed.md`\n68: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/plan-seed.json`\n69: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/plan-validation-report.md`\n70: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/plan-validation-report.json`\n71: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix-template.md`\n72: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix-template.json`\n73: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix.md`\n74: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix.json`\n75: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix-report.md`\n76: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix-report.json`\n77: - `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inpu